8. Get Single User — Not Found

// Request
GET http://localhost:8000/users/999

// Response 404
{ "error": "User 999 not found" }

---
9. Create User

// Request
POST http://localhost:8000/users
{
  "name": "Dave Lee",
  "email": "dave@example.com",
  "age": 25,
  "active": true,
  "tags": ["tester"],
  "roles": [{ "id": 5, "name": "viewer", "level": 1, "permissions": ["read"] }]
}

// Response 201  (id is auto-assigned)
{
  "id": 4,
  "name": "Dave Lee",
  "email": "dave@example.com",
  "age": 25,
  "active": true,
  "tags": ["tester"],
  "roles": [{ "id": 5, "name": "viewer", "level": 1, "permissions": ["read"] }]
}

---
10. Replace User — Full Update (PUT)

// Request
PUT http://localhost:8000/users/1
{
  "name": "Alice Updated",
  "email": "alice-new@example.com",
  "age": 35,
  "active": false
}

// Response 200  (entire object is replaced — fields not sent are gone)
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Alice Updated",
  "email": "alice-new@example.com",
  "age": 35,
  "active": false
}

---
11. Replace User — Not Found (PUT)

// Request
PUT http://localhost:8000/users/999
{ "name": "Ghost" }

// Response 404
{ "error": "User 999 not found" }

---
12. Update User — Partial Update (PATCH)

// Request
PATCH http://localhost:8000/users/2
{ "active": false }

// Response 200  (only active changed, all other fields preserved)
{
  "id": 2,
  "name": "Bob Martinez",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "age": 28,
  "active": false,
  "score": 84.1,
  "phone": null,
  ...
}

---
13. Update User — Not Found (PATCH)

// Request
PATCH http://localhost:8000/users/999
{ "active": false }

// Response 404
{ "error": "User 999 not found" }

